{
  "answer": "**The Foundation of Righteousness:** Surah Al-Baqarah 2:177 defines true righteousness not merely as an outward action, but as firmly believing in God, the Last Day, the angels, the Book, and the prophets [1]. Conversely, Surah An-Nisa 4:136 warns that whoever disbelieves in the Last Day, along with God and His revelations, has gone completely astray [2].\n\n**The Promise of Salvation:** Surah Al-Baqarah 2:62 and Surah Al-Ma'idah 5:69 offer a direct promise that anyone who believes in God and the Last Day and does righteous deeds will be rewarded by their Lord, and they will experience no fear or grief [3, 4]. \n\n**The Certainty of Resurrection:** Surah Al-Hajj 22:7 provides the absolute guarantee that the Hour is coming without a doubt, and that God will resurrect everyone in their graves [5]. Surah At-Taghabun 64:7 directly addresses deniers, commanding the Prophet to swear by God: \"Yes, by my Lord, you will surely be resurrected; then you will surely be informed of what you did\" [6].\n\n**The Guide for Worldly Actions:** In the sources, belief in the Last Day directly informs how believers live their lives. It is a prerequisite for those who maintain the mosques of God [7]. It also drives the believers to strive in the cause of God with their wealth and lives [8] and prevents them from having affection for those who oppose God and His Messenger [9].",
  "conversation_id": "b75c54d4-0ca8-4686-8f68-eef116d359e6",
